Date: Wed, 12 Nov 97 13:13:24 -0700
From: george_haas@mail.fws.gov
I have no information concerning bat urine as a source of infection, but I
do have experience with cave bats and urine [from about 10 years ago. You
get the aerosol effect and in some situations (cave entrances for example
with thousands of bats) it feels like a gentle but steady rain. I am not
aware of a rabies threat posed by this source.
--
George Haas
e-mail: george_haas@mail.fws.gov

